posts.raw_content:
I accepted Jesus Christ as my Lord and Savior. God saved me. I’m in a really bad situation right now and lost myself. I didn’t see a way out. I prayed to God for weeks, without expectation, just blind faith. I just felt his presence and felt his love. I asked him to please forgive my sins and cried. He was not judgmental at all - he was so loving and understanding. I knew that he worked in mysterious ways and an answer to my problem would come, but probably not in a conventional way. I just kept my faith, praying without expectation.

And it happened. Today it happened and my prayer was answered. This was big, it was a monumental moment of clarity. Purely divine. I just wanted to share with you guys because I’ve never even read the Bible. God is real - he meets you where you’re at. Just keep your faith and know that the path to your prayer being answered may not be conventional. 

Thank you for letting me share. 🙏
